3 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Judicial performance evaluations. (1) Beginning in 2026, the
4 commission shall prepare:
5 (a) a midterm performance evaluation for each district court judge during the third year of the
6 judge’s term;
7 (b) a preelection performance evaluation for each district court judge during the fifth year of the
8 judge's term;
9 (c) a midterm performance evaluation for each justice of the Montana supreme court during the
10 third year of the justice’s term;
11 (d) a preelection performance evaluation for each supreme court justice during the seventh year of
12 the justice's term; and
13 (e) a preelection performance evaluation for each judge appointed to a vacancy during the year
14 prior to the last year of the judge's current term.
15 (2) The performance evaluation for a judge under subsection (1) may consider only the information
16 listed in subsections (3) and (4). The performance evaluation must give primary emphasis to information
17 gathered since the judge's election or appointment to the judge's current term in office.
18 (3) The information a performance evaluation must consider is as follows:
19 (a) the results of the judge’s most recent judicial performance survey conducted in accordance
20 with [section 5];
21 (b) information acquired by observation of the judge's conduct in the courtroom;
22 (c) the judge’s judicial disciplinary record, if any;
23 (d) public comment directed toward SOLICITED BY the commission whether solicited or unsolicited;
24 (e) information from any earlier judicial performance evaluation of the judge, except that the
25 commission shall rely primarily on information gathered subsequent to the last judicial election; and
26 (f) any other factor the commission considers relevant to evaluating the judge’s performance and
27 previously authorized as a permissible factor by rule.
